---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Live Dashboards">

<section class="page-header">
  <div class="live-dot"></div>
  <h1>Live Dashboards</h1>
  <p>Real metrics from the running GKE cluster. Grafana dashboards powered by Google Managed Prometheus.</p>
</section>

<section class="dashboards">
  <div class="dash-inner">

    <div class="dash-section">
      <h2>Agent Platform Overview</h2>
      <p class="dash-desc">Agent runs, failure rates, token usage, and gateway health — the four numbers that matter.</p>
      <div class="grafana-embed">
        <!-- Replace GRAFANA_URL with your actual Grafana instance URL -->
        <!-- The dashboard UID is "sympozium-overview" from our grafana-dashboard.json -->
        <iframe
          src="GRAFANA_URL/d/sympozium-overview/sympozium-ai-agent-platform?orgId=1&from=now-6h&to=now&theme=dark&kiosk"
          width="100%"
          height="600"
          frameborder="0"
          loading="lazy"
        ></iframe>
        <div class="embed-fallback">
          <p>Dashboard loading... If this doesn't appear, ensure Grafana is configured for anonymous access.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-section">
      <h2>Sympozium Web UI</h2>
      <p class="dash-desc">The built-in management console — instance status, agent runs, personas, skills, and policies.</p>
      <div class="grafana-embed">
        <!-- Replace with the actual Sympozium API Server web UI URL -->
        <iframe
          src="SYMPOZIUM_API_URL/ui"
          width="100%"
          height="700"
          frameborder="0"
          loading="lazy"
        ></iframe>
        <div class="embed-fallback">
          <p>Web UI loading... The API server serves the React dashboard at /ui.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="metrics-grid">
      <h2>Key Metrics Explained</h2>

      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-name">sympozium_agent_runs_total</div>
        <div class="metric-type">Counter</div>
        <p>Every agent execution — broken down by model (gemini-2.5-pro, gemma-3-27b-it, etc.), status (success/failed), and instance name. The primary throughput indicator.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-name">gen_ai.usage.output_tokens_total</div>
        <div class="metric-type">Counter</div>
        <p>Output tokens generated by model. Directly correlates with Vertex AI cost. The dashboard shows tokens/minute by model tier so you can see where spend is going.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-name">sympozium_agent_run_duration</div>
        <div class="metric-type">Histogram</div>
        <p>End-to-end agent execution time in milliseconds. The dashboard shows P50, P95, and P99 to catch tail latency issues — especially important for interactive channels.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-name">sympozium_tool_invocations_total</div>
        <div class="metric-type">Counter</div>
        <p>Every tool/skill sidecar call, by tool name and status. Shows which tools agents use most and which are failing — essential for debugging complex multi-step agent runs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-name">sympozium_gateway_ready</div>
        <div class="metric-type">Gauge</div>
        <p>Web endpoint gateway readiness. When this drops to 0, the OpenAI-compatible API is down. Alerts fire after 5 minutes of not-ready state.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="metric-card">
        <div class="metric-name">sympozium_errors_total</div>
        <div class="metric-type">Counter</div>
        <p>Unhandled errors across all components. Spikes here correlate with agent failures and should be investigated alongside the failure rate panel.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dash-section">
      <h2>Alert Rules</h2>
      <p class="dash-desc">Built-in alerting via GMP Rules CRD. These fire automatically when thresholds are breached.</p>

      <table class="alert-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Alert</th>
            <th>Condition</th>
            <th>Severity</th>
            <th>Why It Matters</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>AgentRunFailureRateHigh</code></td>
            <td>&gt;25% failure rate over 5m</td>
            <td><span class="sev sev-warn">warning</span></td>
            <td>Agents are failing — check Vertex AI quota, model availability, or prompt issues</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>AgentRunFailureRateCritical</code></td>
            <td>&gt;50% failure rate over 5m</td>
            <td><span class="sev sev-crit">critical</span></td>
            <td>Majority of runs failing — likely a platform-level issue, not individual agents</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>TokenBudgetCritical</code></td>
            <td>&gt;2M output tokens/hr</td>
            <td><span class="sev sev-crit">critical</span></td>
            <td>Significant Vertex AI spend — a runaway agent or unexpected traffic spike</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>AgentRunLatencyHigh</code></td>
            <td>P95 &gt;2min over 10m</td>
            <td><span class="sev sev-warn">warning</span></td>
            <td>Interactive users are waiting too long — check model load or prompt complexity</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>ToolErrorRateHigh</code></td>
            <td>&gt;30% tool errors over 5m</td>
            <td><span class="sev sev-warn">warning</span></td>
            <td>A specific tool sidecar is broken — check RBAC, image pull, or API connectivity</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .page-header { padding: 80px 24px 40px; text-align: center; position: relative; }
  .page-header h1 { font-size: 48px; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -1px; }
  .page-header p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 12px; font-size: 18px; }
  .live-dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; background: var(--gcp-green); border-radius: 50%; margin: 0 auto 16px; animation: pulse 2s infinite; }
  @keyframes pulse { 0%, 100% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(52,168,83,0.4); } 50% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 10px rgba(52,168,83,0); } }

  .dashboards { padding: 0 24px 80px; }
  .dash-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .dash-section { margin-bottom: 60px; }
  .dash-section h2 { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .dash-desc { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 24px; }

  .grafana-embed { background: var(--surface-2); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; position: relative; }
  .grafana-embed iframe { display: block; border: none; min-height: 500px; }
  .embed-fallback { position: absolute; inset: 0; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; z-index: -1; }
  .embed-fallback p { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 14px; }

  .metrics-grid { margin-top: 60px; }
  .metrics-grid h2 { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .metric-card { background: var(--surface-2); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; gap: 8px; }
  .metric-name { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--gcp-blue); grid-column: 1; }
  .metric-type { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); background: var(--surface-3); padding: 2px 10px; border-radius: 4px; height: fit-content; }
  .metric-card p { grid-column: 1 / -1; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 4px; }

  .alert-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 16px; }
  .alert-table th { text-align: left; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; padding: 12px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .alert-table td { padding: 14px 16px; font-size: 13px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); vertical-align: top; }
  .alert-table code { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gcp-blue); }
  .sev { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .sev-warn { background: rgba(251,188,4,0.15); color: var(--gcp-yellow); }
  .sev-crit { background: rgba(234,67,53,0.15); color: var(--gcp-red); }
</style>

</Base>
